
Overview of noun strap

The noun strap has 4 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (2) strap -- (an elongated leather strip (or a strip of similar material) for binding things together or holding something in position)
2. strap -- (hanger consisting of a loop of leather suspended from the ceiling of a bus or train; passengers hold onto it)
3. strap, shoulder strap -- (a band that goes over the shoulder and supports a garment or bag)
4. strap -- (whip consisting of a strip of leather used in flogging)

Overview of verb strap

The verb strap has 4 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (1) strap -- (tie with a strap)
2. flog, welt, whip, lather, lash, slash, strap, trounce -- (beat severely with a whip or rod; "The teacher often flogged the students"; "The children were severely trounced")
3. strap -- (sharpen with a strap; "strap a razor")
4. strap -- (secure (a sprained joint) with a strap)
